==Ancient Greek==

===References===
*[[Strong's concordance]] number:  [http://www.biblestudytools.net/Lexicons/Greek/grk.cgi?number=4625&version=kjv G4625] 

===Pronunciation===
*σκάνδαλον / skandalon / skan'-dal-on
=== Etymology ===

*A “[[scandal]]”; probably from a derivative of [[κάμπτω]] {{GG|2578}}; a trap stick (bent sapling), that is, [[snare]] (figuratively cause of displeasure or sin): 
=== Noun ===
occasion to fall (of stumbling), [[offence]], thing that offends, stumbling-block.